# 🏦 ParaBank Banking App Testing

## 📄 Project Overview

This project focuses on functional and negative testing of the ParaBank demo online banking application. The goal is to ensure that critical banking features work reliably and securely.

---

## 💡 Objectives

- Validate key banking workflows such as login, account management, transactions, and profile updates.
- Apply systematic test design techniques for thorough coverage.
- Document clear and reusable test cases for each user story.

---

## ✅ Scope

### Key User Stories Covered

- User Login Functionality
- Change Personal Information
- View Account Balance
- Open New Account
- Transfer Funds with Validation
- Logout Functionality
- And more

---

## 🧰 Test Design Techniques

- **Equivalence Partitioning (EP)**
- **Boundary Value Analysis (BVA)**
- **State Transition Testing (ST)**

Each user story includes detailed test cases and tables summarizing EP and ST coverage where applicable.

---

## 📄 Deliverables

- Detailed user stories and descriptions
- Comprehensive test cases with preconditions, steps, and expected results
- Test design technique documentation (EP, BVA, ST)
- Test summary reports (PDFs per user story)

---

## 🛠️ Tools Used

- **TestMonitor** for test management and tracking
- **ParaBank demo application** (https://parabank.parasoft.com/parabank/index.htm)
- Test design diagrams and supporting documentation

---

## 💬 Key Highlights

- Covered both positive and negative test scenarios
- Used structured techniques for thorough validation
- Delivered clear, professional documentation to simulate real-world QA practices

